Description: Drissa, I can hardly say enough about this doeling. She is a very flashy doe that is strong in general appearance. She has amazing rib spacing. She is strong in feet and legs, and is long and deep bodied. She is always a joy to work with as well.

Sorella is a very strong doe. She is thick through the shoulders, and has a very wide rump. She has become a very well balanced doe, during her second year! She is always the first to the milk stand. She has such a sweet personality to go with her, easily one of people's favorites when they meet the herd.

 

Dam: Rancho-Snowfall Surya

 

Maternal Granddam: Heart Mt Sumaya

Photo courtesy of Rancho-Snowfall Dairy Goats.

Paternal Granddam: Rancho-Snowfall Tulsa Time

Photo courtesy of Rancho-Snowfall Dairy Goats.

Karribean is a very long bodied doe. I am so excited to see how this girl grows up!! She freshen as a yearling and I am pleased with the way she looks. She has her mother's mammary, which was the appraiser's favorite udder last year!
ShowPlacings: Reserve Champion Overall Sr. Doe (won as a milking yearling)

Description:
I was very excited the day Olivia joined the herd. She is a long bodied doe, who I am excited to see freshen. She will be remaining a dry yearling for 2020.
Olivia is a very sweet doe and steals the hearts of everyone who meets her (even those who do not like goats).
